<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="270" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1070,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,1178,1203]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[758,885,1179,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[758,885,1179,1203]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hendel (
<number box="[1005,1064,1179,1203]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1914.0">1914</number>
b, S. 
<number box="[1130,1173,1179,1203]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="308.0">308</number>
) described 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male, which, as he mentioned in description, has a label and depositary: 
<number box="[1351,1386,1215,1239]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="13.0">13</number>
aus 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,1252,1275]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Formosa</collectingCountry>
, Kosempo (leg. H.Sauter), im Deutsch. Ent. Nat. Museum. He meant Deutschen Entomologischen National-Museum zu Berlin, later Deutsches Entomologisches Institut (Eberswalde, DEI), now Senckenberg Deutsches Entomologisches Institut Müncheberg. In SDEI, due to kindly help of Dr. Frank Menzel, all the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,274,1361,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,1361,1384]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
material was looked through. A 
<typeStatus box="[651,699,1361,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[854,1081,1360,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[854,1081,1360,1384]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent there. It also was not listed by Rohlfien and Ewald (
<number box="[495,556,1396,1420]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1972.0">1972</number>
). Based on our own search and information from Dr. Joachim Ziegler the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1397,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
specimen is also absent in Museum für Naturkunde der Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin. Dr. Peter Sehnal from Naturhistorisches Museum Wien (NHMW) kindly inform us, that 
<typeStatus box="[924,972,1469,1493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1246,1469,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[1017,1246,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent in the Hendel’s collection in Vienna; however there are non-type specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1205,1504,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[979,1205,1504,1528]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with label &quot;Sokutsu 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,1540,1564]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Formosa</collectingCountry>
&quot; (
<number box="[276,291,1540,1564]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
3, 2 Ƥ).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1070,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
Due to absence of the 
<typeStatus box="[452,503,1577,1601]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
, in the diagnostics of 
<taxonomicName box="[748,974,1576,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[748,974,1576,1600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Pterogenia luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we follow Hendel’s (
<number box="[1217,1275,1576,1600]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1914.0">1914</number>
b) description. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,284,1613,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrica" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,284,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. tenebrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[291,370,1613,1636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<emphasis box="[518,636,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. l u c t u o s a</emphasis>
in having the brown spot between antennal base and eye and by lunule dark brown (lunule yellow in 
<taxonomicName box="[507,634,1648,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[507,634,1648,1672]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In wing color pattern the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1396,1648,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis box="[1269,1396,1648,1672]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by prediscal wing band (short transverse band beginning from R 
<number box="[832,840,1700,1714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1.0">1</number>
apex) merging with stigmatal wing band (broad band beginning from Sc apex) in r 
<number box="[470,478,1738,1752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[487,494,1738,1752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="5.0">5</number>
cell (
<figureCitation box="[556,622,1723,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1959,1982]" captionTargetBox="[207,1345,196,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[197,1389,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pterogenia tenebrica sp. nov., female holotype; a—habitus, lateral view, b—head and thorax, dorsal view; chead, lateral view; d—head, anterior view; e—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248403/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[608,622,1723,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
e). In 
<emphasis box="[687,805,1723,1747]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. l u c t u o s a</emphasis>
prediscal band does not reach stigmatal one (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1381,1723,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1959,1982]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,205,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1389,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pterogenia luctuosa Hendel, 1914, male; a—habitus, lateral view, b—head and thorax, dorsal view; c—head, lateral view; d—head, anterior view; e—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248405/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[1366,1381,1723,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
e). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. luctuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[303,438,1762,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrica" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis box="[303,438,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. tenebrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[445,525,1763,1786]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may be confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Frey" authorityName="Frey" box="[791,981,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamifera">
<emphasis box="[791,921,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. hamifera</emphasis>
Frey
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1132,1763,1786]" name="Myanmar" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Burma</collectingCountry>
. The transverse wing band beginning from R 
<number box="[349,357,1813,1827]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[366,373,1813,1827]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="3.0">3</number>
apex is contiguous in 
<taxonomicName box="[624,752,1798,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamifera">
<emphasis box="[624,752,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. hamifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[768,836,1798,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1007,1030]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,985]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,986]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. a— Pterogenia hamifera Frey, 1930, wing (from Frey’s figure 3, Taf. 1); b— Neohemigaster minuspicta Hennig, 1940, wing (Typus); c— Neohemigaster flavopicta Hennig, 1940, wing (Typus); d— Neohemigaster ornata Hennig, 1940, wing (Typus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[820,836,1798,1822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
a), but broken into separate spots in 
<emphasis box="[1239,1357,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. l u c t u o s a</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Pterogenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">P. tenebrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1070,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
We marked female as a 
<typeStatus box="[482,580,1872,1896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">holotype</typeStatus>
in this case, because genitals have never been used to separate species in these genera. All species are well separated by characters of external morphology (in which males and females do not differ). McAlpine, describing 
<taxonomicName box="[535,717,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platystomatidae</taxonomicName>
, often marked female as a 
<typeStatus box="[1024,1122,1944,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">holotype</typeStatus>
in the presence of males in 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1982,2006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
